com.ibm.xmi.framework
Class UML2Schema

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--com.ibm.xmi.framework.UML2Schema
public class UML2Schema
extends java.lang.Object

This program lets you convert a UML 1.1 XMI 1.0 file to an XMI schema.

You have two choices for the schemas that are produced: XMI 1.1 schemas, which are almost equivalent to XMI DTDs, and XMI 2.0 schemas, which put all of the XMI elements and attributes in a namespace to prevent potential name collisions.

Each namespace is put in a separate schema; if there are no namespaces, one schema is generated with no target namespace.

The XMI 2.0 schemas that are produced use an xmi:Any type for elements that can allow any content and any attributes; this type is not in the current XMI 2.0 specification. Our xmi20.xsd that we include in the Framework examples includes it.
